Goal

The "Furry Heaven" app is a platform designed to connect pet owners with experienced and caring pet sitters. It aims to provide a reliable and convenient way for pet owners to find trustworthy individuals who can take care of their pets when they are unable to do so themselves.


The app includes features such as profiles of pet sitters, reviews from other users, scheduling capabilities, even options for pet owners to communicate directly with sitters. Overall, it serves as a bridge between pet owners needing pet sitting services and individuals willing to provide such care

Context

What is Furry Heaven ?

Problem Discovery

Pet Owners' Dilemma: Solving the Search for Trusted Pet Sitters

Families come in all shapes and sizes, and for many Americans, pets are an integral part of their family.

Millennials represent the largest segment of pet owners, making up 32% of the population. Despite their busy and hardworking lifestyles, often dubbed the "burnout generation," millennials still prioritize pet ownership.

Traveling for work or leisure is a common part of their lives, and their primary concern during these times is, "Who will take care of Max, my precious poodle?"

Research Process

Empathy Mapping

To uncover the frustrations and issues pet owners face when searching for a pet sitter

To develop solutions for pet owners seeking a safe and comfortable place for their pets while traveling.

An app designed for pet owners to easily find trusted caregivers for their pets while they are busy or traveling.

Idea

Through user interviews, mapped out the potential thoughts, actions, feelings, and expressions of users.

This process provided a deeper understanding of their needs, emotions, pain points, and experiences.

Persona

By consulting pet parents, created user personas to shape design decisions.

Competitor Research

Researched existing pet care products before creating solutions.

A popular app that connects pet owners with pet sitters.

Includes features like GPS tracking and real-time updates for pet owners.

Charges a service fee or commission for each booking.

Offers additional paid features such as premium placement in search results or enhanced visibility for providers.

Issues with trust and safety between pet owners and sitters.

Challenges in maintaining consistent service quality across a diverse network of providers.

Lack of Verification

Minimal customer support and recourse for users experiencing issues.

Constraints on space and availability, especially during peak seasons.

Concerns about the stress and anxiety pets may experience in a kennel environment.

It indirectly contribute to the competition by providing a platform for individuals or businesses to offer pet care services.

Direct connection with local pet owners and service providers

Users can post pet care services for free, with options for paid advertisements or promotions to increase visibility.

A traditional kennel is a facility where pet owners can board their animals temporarily, providing shelter, basic care, and sometimes recreational activities

Offers a controlled environment with professional staff and secure facilities.

Often provides discounts or perks for repeat customers or long-term boarding arrangements.

After extensive review of reports, product reviews, competitive analysis, and browsing various websites and app stores, it became evident that pet care services are widely established globally. There are numerous apps and websites offering services like dog walking, dog boarding, and pet sitting. However, while many apps facilitate connections between pet owners and sitters, the process of choosing the right pet sitter can be challenging and time-consuming.

Goal: Selina Aniston want to find a place for Max when she is on a business trip

Selina Aniston

Bio

Wants & Needs

Selina Aniston is a Product Designer for a biomedical startup. She lives in a small apartment with her beloved dog, Max. Her work demands most of her time, so she values convenience and efficiency in all aspects of her life, especially when it comes to caring for Max.

Needs dependable and trustworthy pet sitters who can provide excellent care for Max in her absence.

Loves her dog.

Uses app for everything.

Looking for fast and convenient service.

To have all in user generated content platform as per pet owners need.(day care, walking etc)

Include advanced search filters (e.g., location, availability, services offered) to help narrow down options quickly.

Showcase verified reviews and ratings from other pet owners.

Offer a chat feature for direct communication with potential sitters.

Simplify the booking process with a user-friendly interface.

Enable real-time updates and photos of the pet’s well-being.

Offer a summary of the pet’s stay and activities.


Encourage repeat bookings with loyalty rewards or discounts.

Analyzed Feedback

Results

High Fidelity Wireframes

After I conducted user interviews with 7-10 users with the mid-fidelity prototypes, the findings went in both directions, some positive and some negative. Most positive insights highlighted the ease of use and clarity through the process.

Few users wanted to have a more approachable brand look or feel and I made sure to refine the lean branding to apply to the final high fidelity prototype.

“I love that I have a clear idea of where I am in the process due to the status bar”

Pet Sitter Screen

Furry Heaven is currently a platform that allows pet owners to find sitters for their specific needs at any time and location. Looking to the future, the platform aims to expand its services to facilitate the booking of sitter services.


Furry Heaven plans to provide additional support and protections for sitters, ensuring they can earn money in a fair and secure environment.


The platform will enable pet owners to track the location of their pets during walks in real-time. These advancements will enhance trust and transparency between pet owners and sitters. The goal is to create a more balanced and beneficial experience for both pet owners and sitters.

Minimal customer support and recourse for users experiencing issues.

After extensive review of reports, product reviews, competitive analysis, and browsing various websites and app stores, it became evident that pet care services are widely established globally. There are numerous apps and websites offering services like dog walking, dog boarding, and pet sitting. However, while many apps facilitate connections between pet owners and sitters, the process of choosing the right pet sitter can be challenging and time-consuming.

Pet Sitter Screen

Furry Heaven is currently a platform that allows pet owners to find sitters for their specific needs at any time and location. Looking to the future, the platform aims to expand its services to facilitate the booking of sitter services.


Furry Heaven plans to provide additional support and protections for sitters, ensuring they can earn money in a fair and secure environment.


The platform will enable pet owners to track the location of their pets during walks in real-time. These advancements will enhance trust and transparency between pet owners and sitters. The goal is to create a more balanced and beneficial experience for both pet owners and sitters.


Goal

The "Furry Heaven" app is a platform designed to connect pet owners with experienced and caring pet sitters. It aims to provide a reliable and convenient way for pet owners to find trustworthy individuals who can take care of their pets when they are unable to do so themselves.


The app includes features such as profiles of pet sitters, reviews from other users, scheduling capabilities, even options for pet owners to communicate directly with sitters. Overall, it serves as a bridge between pet owners needing pet sitting services and individuals willing to provide such care

Context

What is Furry Heaven ?

Problem Discovery

Pet Owners' Dilemma: Solving the Search for Trusted Pet Sitters

Families come in all shapes and sizes, and for many Americans, pets are an integral part of their family.

Millennials represent the largest segment of pet owners, making up 32% of the population. Despite their busy and hardworking lifestyles, often dubbed the "burnout generation," millennials still prioritize pet ownership.

Traveling for work or leisure is a common part of their lives, and their primary concern during these times is, "Who will take care of Max, my precious poodle?"

Research Process

Empathy Mapping

To uncover the frustrations and issues pet owners face when searching for a pet sitter

To develop solutions for pet owners seeking a safe and comfortable place for their pets while traveling.

An app designed for pet owners to easily find trusted caregivers for their pets while they are busy or traveling.

Idea

Through user interviews, mapped out the potential thoughts, actions, feelings, and expressions of users.

This process provided a deeper understanding of their needs, emotions, pain points, and experiences.

Persona

By consulting pet parents, created user personas to shape design decisions.

Competitor Research

Researched existing pet care products before creating solutions.
